e damage WHILE healing.  Do you use a group heal or individual heals?  If there are 2 MoBs, how do you balance your heals?  There is a lot that goes on in ToV or Western Wastes that vclerics need to be conscious of.  It's not as simple as point and click.  You  need to know how heals affect different people in your group and how many HP your tanks have.  This requires EXPERIENCE and ALWAYS being aware of your group or even outside cries for help.<br><br>VP:<br><br>Here you have an entirely different view on life and death.  As a cleric you MUST remain sharp and alert.  Manna efficiency is the key here.  I have had to literally calculate how I would use each of my healing spells.  I try to get my timing down to a science so that my heals are the most efficient.  Case in point...  I was with KEG recently and had a few tanks in my group with Krieger as the MT.  He is a lvl 60 warrior with full Kael armor I believe.  He had 5450 HP or so.  There were times when he was down to his last 200 HP before my CH landed.  It wasn't an accident... that's timing.  I did it 3-4 times in 2 hours.  If you call that boring, ask Krieger how boring that was to see &quot;You have been healed for 5300 Hit Points...&quot;  It takes concentration and knowledge of how your group takes damage.<br><br>Various Other Zones...<br><br>Depending on where you go, your job as a cleric changes.  I have been in groups where I have needed to heal, stun, root, and nuke.  Now that is definitely not ideal, but clerics need to balance out what they do and how they do it.  They also need to know when it's really time to position yourself to camp in disasters.<br><br>I am not getting into an argument about who is the best class.  They are ALL important.  But I am sick of people telling me that being a cleric is boring.  I am the life blood of a group.  That is a lot of pressure.  The best thing that happened to casters was the ability to disrupt spells by ducking!  How many times have you clerics began casting CH when all of a sudden your chanter starts dropping like a lead weight.  With 5 seconds left in the CH that chanter will be dead.  Clerics need to decide who dies when desperate times come.  Example:  You are low mana, your group is at 40% or lower.  You have a choice to heal your MT or Enchanter and you are in the Chef area of Sebillis with about 4 MoBs there.  I KNOW this has happened to you at least once.  Maybe someone overpulled... who knows, but you are there and need to make a decision.  Someone is going to die.  Who dies?  The tank of course!  Who is gonna keep those 4 MoBs sleepy while you res people?  The chanter.  See?  Decisions...<br><br>Anyways....<br><br>Clerics are not a boring class.  Play a lvl 55+ cleric and tell me different. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uoriathin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oriathin</A> at: 11/28/01 9:03:43 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/urexron.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rexron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Pie Guy </span><br>  Posts: 314<br> <font color=#333333>(11/28/01 10:13:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=58.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ohhh to be a cleric...</span><hr size=1> Love the post.  I am actually going to re-read it later.<br><br>Yeah, i will say that game changes again at 56 or so.<br><br>Last night we did our 1st real foray into West Wastes.  A few have gone there before, but this was the 1st time we went as a guild to raid.  Nothing like Pulling two dragons, one that casts silence, both that cast a DOT that has to do about 500 damage a dick (I had 2500 hp and went down about 1/5th health every few seconds).  And you're right.  Do you "Pants" heal (Area heal on most if not all of the cler